         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 2649, recto: (1) Kalasiris, son of Horus, and his colleagues, (2) the [agents] of the necropolis, say: (3) We are paid the tax of the chief of the necropolis of (4) Pasemis, son of Pamonthes, son of [Meswer], which amounts to 3 staters / (5) 1 stater, 1 kite / 3 staters again. Written in year 43, (6) Tybi 12, of Caesar.</ab>
